      "te_emails": [],
      "intent_thread_url": "https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/d/msgid/blink-dev/67b8a89e.2b0a0220.175b17.0a0c.GAE%40google.com",
      "announcement_url": null,
      "experiment_goals": "This feature has a number of moving parts (see https://wicg.github.io/signature-based-sri/#overview), and while they make sense on paper, it will be interesting to learn whether the system as a whole is deployable at scale. Ideally, we'll learn things about developer flows and performance, and also confirm our understanding of the threat models developers want this mechanism to solve.\n\nNote, though, that this feature's implementation is split across the network service (which handles signature parsing and verification) and Blink (which handles digest calculation and checks against relevant integrity metadata). We have a fairly straightforward way of testing client-initiated integrity checks (which is the core of the feature), but server-initiated checks will be difficult to support given the network services' lack of clarity about whether or not the trial is enabled in the context from which a request was initiated.",
      "experiment_risks": "When the feature is disabled, sites delivering `<script integrity>` attributes containing `ed25519-...` public keys will result in parse errors. This will not create any behavioral change on the page, but would show up as a console warning.\n\nThe feature is otherwise ephemeral, its effects constrained to a single page-load and/or resource request. Disabling the experiment should not leave anyone in a broken state.",
      "origin_trial_id": "2704974526189404161",
      "origin_trial_feedback_url": null,
      "ot_action_requested": false,
      "ot_approval_buganizer_component": null,
